Windows :

Step-1 : Install Java (JDK) 
1. Install JDK 17

1.2 Verify Java Installation:
- Open Powershell 
  - java -version
      - You shoulf see something like 17.x 

1.3 Set JAVA_HOME 
  1. - Open Start-> "Environment variable" -> Edit the system Environment variable -> Environment variables 
  2. - Under System variable - New 

  - Variable_name : JAVA_HOME
  - variable_value : C://Program files\java\jdk-17 

  3. Edit Path (System variable) : Add 
    .%JAVA_HOME%\bin

  Verify (New Poweshell )

  echo $env:JAVA_HOME 
  java -version 


Step 2 : Install Python 3.11 

    - Install 3.11 from python.org 
    - Add python path 
    
  Powershell

  Python --version 
  pip --version 


Step 3: Download apache spark (3.5.8)

  Extarct :

  C:\Spark\ 

  So your final folder :

  C:\spark\spark 3.5.8-bin-hadoop3 

Step 4 : Set Spark_Home +Path 

Open Environment variable :
4.1 Add spark_Home 
  - Under system variable -> New 
  - Name : SPARK_HOME 
  - value : C:\spark\spark 3.5.8-bin-hadoop3 

  4.2 Spark Path 

  Edit path -> Add:
  .%SPARK_HOME%\bin

-- Verify 
echo $env:SPARK_HOME
spark-submit --version 
pyspark --version 


Step 5 : Install Pyspark 




